reviewText: Great Action Movies. Tom Cruise,& a Collection of Different, but Excellent Actors for each film. I liked them all. MI 5- Rogue Nation is the Best of them all. See it in Theaters Now!.

The series was more like a con where as these movies are more destruction. What do these movies have in common with the original series, the abbriviation IMF and rubber masks. Too much fighting, shooting, killing. Where is the technical gadgets and clean and quiet get away like in the series Bruce Geller created. I guess a movie where some infiltrate a situation with acting a part while others use gadgetry to set up a trap or retrieve an item, would take too much thought on the part of the writers.
Product came on time.service  was good. And movies are great.

I really like the Mission: Impossible Collection. As soon as I got this set I started watching the movies. I would recommend this movie collection to anyone who is a fan of spy thrillers and action movies. I will say that this movie collection is definitely worth the price and I am pleased with my purchase.
great movies if your into Tom Cruise

Very mediocre plot, poor acting and so on... After watching all of Bond, MI does not impress much. A lot like the recent Craig's Bond: too much running around and 20-minute fights. The DVD and packaging are good though.

They definitely should have stopped at three in this series. The fourth movie is lacking in the script area and the movie flow area. The first three are pretty good with the third one being the best.

binge watching these is the best way to watch them- but I'll never forgive the screenwriters for making Jim Phelps the bad guy in MI-1 and married to what amounts to be a 12 yr old (they could have made it his daughter), but the rest of the film with Ving Raymes makes up for it, somewhat, and Vanessa Redgrave is both brilliant and delicious in her limited role- the rest of the bunch is fun, serious and entertaining.
they are great and i like having them all together.
